# Python Backend Conventions

## Project Structure

The backend is organized as a Python package `curator/` with these subpackages:

- [main.py](mdc:curator/main.py) — Orchestrates startup of all subsystems
- [config.py](mdc:curator/config.py) — Environment variables, paths, constants
- [customers.py](mdc:curator/customers.py) — Customer configurations, cache management
- `brain/` — Claude agent with tool-use loop ([agent.py](mdc:curator/brain/agent.py), [tools.py](mdc:curator/brain/tools.py), [prompts.py](mdc:curator/brain/prompts.py))
- `ingestion/` — Document pipeline ([pipeline.py](mdc:curator/ingestion/pipeline.py), [converters.py](mdc:curator/ingestion/converters.py), [classifier.py](mdc:curator/ingestion/classifier.py))
- `listeners/` — Slack and email listeners ([slack_listener.py](mdc:curator/listeners/slack_listener.py), [email_listener.py](mdc:curator/listeners/email_listener.py))
- `storage/` — Google Drive, Gmail, profiles, event log, conversations
- `search/` — Ripgrep and semantic search
- `scheduler/` — APScheduler-based task store and executor
- `slidebot/` — Weekly update generation
- `web/` — FastAPI dashboard ([app.py](mdc:curator/web/app.py), [index.html](mdc:curator/web/static/index.html))

## Coding Conventions

### Async/Await
- All I/O operations MUST be async
- Use `asyncio.to_thread()` to wrap synchronous library calls (Google API, marker, etc.)
- Never block the event loop with synchronous I/O

### Google API Calls
- Use `threading.local()` for service objects (see [google_auth.py](mdc:curator/storage/google_auth.py))
- Always wrap in `asyncio.to_thread()`
- Apply `@_retry` decorator for transient network errors

### Customer Isolation
- **HARD RULE**: Information between customers MUST NOT leak
- Every agent call, search, storage operation scopes to a single `customer_key`
- Customer data lives in isolated directory trees: `CURATOR_CACHE_DIR / customer_key /`
- Google Drive folders are per-customer subfolders

### Profile System
- Customer-facing profile: `meta/profile.json` — agent can read and update
- Internal-only profile: `meta/internal_profile.json` — UI-only, agent has ZERO access
- **HARD RULE**: Agent tools must NEVER expose internal profile fields (health_score, churn_risk, etc.)

### Error Handling
- Wrap subsystem startups in try/except to ensure resilient startup
- Log exceptions with `logger.exception()` or `logger.warning(..., exc_info=True)`
- Return graceful fallbacks (empty lists, default values) rather than crashing

### Imports
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` at the top of every module
- Group imports: stdlib → third-party → local `curator.*`
- Use lazy imports for heavy modules inside functions when appropriate

### Logging
- Use `logging.getLogger(__name__)` in every module
- Use structured log messages: `logger.info("[%s] Action: %s", customer_key, detail)`
